headlines.description: Albany's Joe Cremo scored 19 of his 22 points in the first half and Maine couldn't recover from a 10-point effort in the first 20 minutes with the Great Danes taking an 84-66 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Albany wins 84-66 after Maine scores 10 in first half

headlines.description: Jarius Lyles scored 21 points and K.J. Maura added 17 on 6-of-7 shooting, including 5 of 6 from 3-point range, to help Maryland-Baltimore County beat UMass Lowell 89-62 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyles, Maura lead UMBC to 89-62 win over UMass Lowell

headlines.description: Junior Robinson sank the winning layup with 15 seconds left in the extra period and Mount St. Mary's edged St. Francis (PA) 81-80 in overtime on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mount St. Mary's edges St. Francis (PA) in OT, 81-80

headlines.description: Geno Crandall poured in 25 points on 10 of 16 shooting and dished eight assists as North Dakota defeated Weber State 89-79 on Saturday as the defending Big Sky champion has won two in a row after going winless for a month.
headlines.shortLinkText: North Dakota defeats Weber St 89-79 for 2nd straight win

headlines.description: Devin Mitchell scored 15 points, Malik Benlevi added 14 more to go with 11 rebounds and Georgia State cruised to its fourth-straight victory with a 72-58 win over Coastal Carolina on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia State pulls away for 72-58 win over Coastal Carolina

headlines.description: Ria'n Holland had 23 points and Stephon Jelks added 13 with 11 rebounds as Mercer won its first Southern Conference game in dominating fashion, thumping Samford 81-50 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mercer gets 1st league win, dominating Samford 81-50

headlines.description: Freshman Abayomi Iyiola had 12 points and 11 rebounds -- his second double-double -- and B.J. Glasford scored 18 points to help Stetson beat USC Upstate 87-69 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iyiola's double-double helps Stetson beat USC Upstate 87-69

headlines.description: Bryce Moore opened the game with a 3-pointer and Josh Davis hit two more as Western Michigan opened on a 13-3 run and never eased up in a 73-58 Mid-America Conference West Division battle with Ball State on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Western Michigan starts fast, rolls past Ball State 73-58

headlines.description: Travin Thibodeaux scored 20 points and New Orleans survived poor shooting for a 61-55 victory over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thibodeaux scores 20 in New Orleans 61-55 triumph

headlines.description: Alex Peacock made his only field goal count, hitting a long, buzzer-beating jumper to lift Texas State to a 72-70 victory over Little Rock on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Peacock's only basket wins it for Texas State 72-70

headlines.description: JD Notae scored 21 points and Devin Harris added 19 points, nine rebounds, seven assists and five steals to help Jacksonville beat Lipscomb 87-69 on Saturday night.
Fletcher Magee drilled a trey to give Wofford a late lead and the Terriers held on to knock Furman from the Southern Conference unbeaten ranks 79-70 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wofford's late run clinches 79-70 win over Furman

headlines.description: Kevon Harris scored 19 points and led four players into double-figure scoring as Stephen F. Austin rolled over Incarnate Word, 83-63 in a Southland Conference battle Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen F. Austin now 4-1, rolls past Incarnate Word, 83-63

headlines.description: Bryson Scott scored 26 points and John Konchar had 13 rebounds and nine assists and Fort Wayne beat Omaha 82-78 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scott leads way in Fort Wayne's 82-78 win over Omaha

headlines.description: Lamontray Harris scored 19 points, including the go-ahead basket late in the second half, and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Morehead State to its first Ohio Valley Conference victory of the season with a 71-67 win over Tennessee-Martin on Saturday night.
Ryan Funk scored 10 of his 13 points in overtime and Marist made just enough free throws down the stretch to hold off Fairfield 95-89 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Funk takes over in OT, Marist tops Fairfield 95-89

headlines.description: Marcus Harris scored a career-best 27 points and Sam Houston State cruised past Houston Baptist 81-68 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sam Houston State cruises past Houston Baptist 81-68

headlines.description: Kyle Allman scored 27 points and Khalil Ahmad added 25 with seven boards as Cal State Fullerton notched its fourth-straight win, beating UC Davis 85-70 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: CS Fullerton cruises to 85-70 win over UC Davis

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
